<worksheet >
    <title>TF-4 Laws of Sines and Cosines</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>Complete both parts to get M. Complete part a with progress on part b to get P.</p>
  </introduction>
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="2.5in">
      <introduction><p>Two hikers leave the same camp at the same time. Hiker A walks at a speed of 3 miles 
        per hour in the direction <m>\text{N } 15^\circ \text{ W}</m>. Hiker B walks at a speed of 4 miles 
        per hour in the direction <m>\text{N } 55^\circ \text{ E}</m>. They both hike for 2 hours.</p></introduction>
        <task><statement><p>Draw a diagram to model this situation.</p></statement></task>
        <task><statement><p>Determine how far apart the hikers are after 2 hours. Give a simplified 
          expression for your answer.</p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>